---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import AudioGuideBlock from "../../components/AudioGuideBlock.astro";
import FloridaProblemTreeGuide from "../../components/FloridaProblemTreeGuide.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Florida Problem Tree Guide"
  description="Learn which Florida trees may become invasive, storm-prone, messy, or risky near homes, pools, fences, pavers, and driveways."
>
  <section class="problem-hero">
    <div class="problem-hero-inner">
      <p>Florida homeowner tool</p>
      <h1>Florida Problem Tree Guide</h1>
      <span>
        Identify trees that may create invasive spread, storm risk, root conflicts,
        messy cleanup, or permit review questions on Florida properties.
      </span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FloridaProblemTreeGuide />

    <AudioGuideBlock
      title="Listen to the 55-second problem tree guide"
      description="A quick audio summary for Florida homeowners reviewing tree risks, access issues, cleanup concerns, and permit questions."
      audioSrc="/audio/florida-problem-tree-guide-audio-guide.mp3"
      audioLabel="Florida Problem Tree Guide audio guide"
    />

  <section class="problem-bottom">
    <div class="bottom-card dark">
      <p>Use this guide when</p>
      <h2>A tree looks manageable today but may become expensive later.</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Roots are lifting pavers, sidewalks, driveway edges, or pool decks.</li>
        <li>Seedlings keep returning after cutting or cleanup.</li>
        <li>Storm-season limbs hang over a roof, fence, road, or utility area.</li>
        <li>Fruit, fronds, pods, or leaf litter create repeated maintenance.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom-card light">
      <p>When to get local guidance</p>
      <h2>Call before cutting if the tree is hazardous, regulated, or hard to access.</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The tree is cracked, leaning, uprooted, or blocking access.</li>
        <li>Removal may involve a protected species, mangrove, wetland, HOA, or city rule.</li>
        <li>Equipment access is limited by gates, fences, pools, or tight side yards.</li>
        <li>The stump or roots could interfere with replanting or hardscape repair.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .problem-hero {
    background: radial-gradient(circle at center, #164b34 0%, #082d20 72%);
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: clamp(5rem, 11vw, 9rem) 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 6px solid #f25a06;
  }

  .problem-hero-inner {
    max-width: 980px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .problem-hero p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: #ffb703;
    font-weight: 900;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  }

  .problem-hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.06em;
  }

  .problem-hero span {
    display: block;
    max-width: 820px;
    margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
    color: #bbf7d0;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .problem-bottom {
    max-width: 1180px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem 8rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .bottom-card {
    border-radius: 2rem;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    box-shadow: 0 18px 50px rgba(15, 63, 42, 0.08);
  }

  .bottom-card p {
    margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .bottom-card h2 {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
  }

  .bottom-card li {
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .bottom-card.dark {
    background: #082d20;
    color: #d1fae5;
  }

  .bottom-card.dark p { color: #ffb703; }
  .bottom-card.dark h2 { color: #fff; }

  .bottom-card.light {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #dbe4df;
    color: #475569;
  }

  .bottom-card.light p { color: #f25a06; }
  .bottom-card.light h2 { color: #0f3f2a; }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .problem-bottom {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
